      "title": "Payson Grotto in Payson, Utah",
      "content_html": "<p><img alt=\"Payson Grotto Pool\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://img.atlasobscura.com/g9u4ZrEus83q5DIzPpg6plkOmF9ctv_4VtmxH9h6jz8/rs:fill:300:200:1/g:ce/q:81/sm:1/scp:1/ar:1/aHR0cHM6Ly9hdGxh/cy1kZXYuczMuYW1h/em9uYXdzLmNvbS91/cGxvYWRzL3BsYWNl/X2ltYWdlcy9hZDQ3/ZDA5Yi1kM2NlLTRm/MDYtOWM5OC03ZGMy/M2IwN2ZmYjE0ZDJi/NzdhM2Y2ZWNmMTg4/NzdfUGF5c29uIEdy/b3R0bzEgKDIpLmpw/Zw.jpg\" width=\"300\" /></p> <p>Grotto Falls is a lovely little gem! A short easy hike leads to a little enclosure with a pool of water (shallow enough for most children) fed by a small waterfall. You can bring a swimsuit and wade while enjoying the lovely surrounding nature. It is also possible to hike to the top of the waterfall.</p>\n<p>Wading is best in the summer because the water is cold, but in the fall the canyon trees light up with yellows, oranges, and reds and is especially beautiful.</p>",
